Here's the recommended implementation using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (source-generated):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data service call
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();
        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // simulate network
        return ("Widget", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties with `PropertyChanged` notification, plus a `LoadCommand` (`IAsyncRelayCommand`).

**XAML usage** — note `x:DataType` at the root for compiled bindings:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="8">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name, FallbackValue='Loading...'}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='Available: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` generates properties + `PropertyChanged` — no manual boilerplate.
- `[RelayCommand]` on `LoadAsync` generates `LoadCommand` with built-in `IsRunning` you can bind to an `ActivityIndicator`.
- `x:DataType` enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- `PropertyChanged` is auto-marshalled to the UI thread, so assigning from the async method is safe.

**NuGet package needed:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.0). Also add this to your `.csproj` to catch binding errors at build time:

```xml
<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>
```
